Data Testing & Validation Document


________________________________________
1. Purpose
This document defines the structured approach to testing and validating data accuracy, completeness, integrity, and quality within AWS systems.
The objective is to:
•	Ensure data correctness before go-live
•	Validate transformations and integrations
•	Reduce operational, regulatory, and reputational risk
•	Provide auditable evidence of validation activities
________________________________________
2. Scope
In Scope
•	AWS services used (e.g., S3, Glue, Redshift, RDS, Lambda, EMR, Athena, etc.)
•	Data ingestion pipelines
•	Transformation logic
•	Reporting outputs
•	Downstream integrations
________________________________________
4. Roles & Responsibilities
Role	Responsibility
Data Engineer	Implement validation scripts, resolve defects
Data SME	Execute test cases, document results
Data Owner	Approve validation criteria
Product SME	Validate business logic and outputs
	
	
________________________________________
5. AWS Architecture Overview
Check architecture including:
•	Data Sources
•	Ingestion (API, Batch, Streaming)
•	Storage (S3 buckets, RDS, Redshift)
•	Transformation (Glue, Lambda, EMR)
•	Consumption (BI tools, APIs)
•	Monitoring (CloudWatch, AWS DQ tools)
________________________________________
6. Data Quality Dimensions
The following dimensions will be tested:
Dimension	Description	Example
Accuracy	Data matches source truth	Balance equals source system
Completeness	No missing required data	No NULL in mandatory fields
Consistency	No conflicting records	Customer ID consistent across systems
Validity	Conforms to format/rules	Date format YYYY-MM-DD
Uniqueness	No unintended duplicates	Unique transaction IDs
Timeliness	Data updated as expected	Daily load completed by 06:00
________________________________________
